        <div type="translation">
            <ab>Greek Ostraka, p. 166 (English)

                              Soter son of Kametis and his brothers have paid to the bank in Diospolis Magna (which Kephalos is in charge of?) for the wine collection of the 39th year of Caesar, thirty-six drachmas of silver, that is, 36 dr. Year 40 of Caesar, Tybi 14. Kephalos son of Epikrates. </ab>
